Privacy Policy - SCRIBZEE® Application and Website
Your notes are valuable and therefore, you can’t imagine throwing away the notebook or journal you just finished. You need to reread the notes you wrote 6 days, 6 months or 6 years ago, refer back to them, reuse them, study them, or share them? But who wants to carry their handwritten notes around with them all the time?
You want to make unlimited use of your notes, you believe that they deserve to be preserved, to be retrieved instantaneously anywhere and at any time, SCRIBZEE® (made up of a smartphone application ("SCRIBZEE® Application") and a website "SCRIBZEE® Website")) is for you, you who want to give your notes a new life.
This is why we’re bridging the gap between handwriting and the digital world. Using your smartphone, SCRIBZEE® allows you to scan and easily save the content of your handwritten notes from compatible notebooks, pads, and diaries (such as Oxford, Hamelin or European) on which the markers allowing the use of the capture technology developed and patented by our engineers are printed.
SCRIBZEE® respects your privacy and your notes. Our commitment is represented by the major following principle to ensure a safe and efficient service: your notes are your property, and we guarantee the security and confidentiality of the notes you scan with SCRIBZEE®.
You can enjoy SCRIBZEE® and the power of your writings with confidence.
1. Introduction
HOLDHAM, a French limited liability company with a share capital of €6,160,000, registered at the Caen Trade and Companies Register under the number 352 998 827, located at 1 rue du Campus 14200 Hérouville Saint Clair, France ("HOLDHAM", "we", "our") is data controller. This means that we decide how we store and use the personal data we collect.
This Privacy Policy describes how we collect and use personal data about SCRIBZEE® users ("you", "your", "yours") in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation of 27 April 2016 ("GDPR") and applicable national laws.
It also describes the legal basis on which we process personal data, the people with whom we share personal data and how it is stored.
It is important that you read this Privacy Policy, as well as any other information notice that we may provide on specific occasions when we collect or process your personal data, so that you know how and why we use your personal data.
By using SCRIBZEE®, you agree to the terms set forth in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with certain terms in this Privacy Policy, please do not use SCRIBZEE®.
2. How is your personal data collected?
We collect personal data in different ways as indicated below.
Data collected during the installation of SCRIBZEE® Application
To use the SCRIBZEE® Application, you must open an account by entering your email address or login using your Facebook or Google account. In the case of opening an account with your email address, you will then receive an email with an activation code allowing you to activate your account.
If you do not provide us with your email address or login with your Google or Facebook account, you will not be able to create an account and access the services offered by SCRIBZEE®.
Warning:
in the event your email address is closed (for example, when you leave a company, if you have used a professional email address), you will no longer be able to access your account and data.
When installing the SCRIBZEE® Application, we also collect the language and country of use indicated in the settings of your smartphone by querying the IPStack service. We collect this information to be able to determine the language to be displayed in SCRIBZEE®, the language we will use to communicate with you and also the location where your data will be stored in our nearest data centres.
Data collected during your use of the SCRIBZEE® Application
We collect personal data directly from you when you use the SCRIBZEE® Application as described below.
When you download your handwritten notes, we collect the titles and the scan date of your notes. This information is collected to allow you to search the titles and dates of your notes using the "search" function in SCRIBZEE®;
If you have chosen to connect your smartphone calendar to the SCRIBZEE® Application, we collect the titles of the events that are recorded in the calendar as well as the start and end dates and times of the events;
We collect information about your smartphone (trademark, model, model version and screen size), the software version installed on the smartphone (Android or iOS version) and the version of the SCRIBZEE® Application installed. This information is collected for statistical analysis and to improve the SCRIBZEE® Application; and
We collect personal data from you when you contact us via the contact form.
In addition, please note that we also collect data to study user traffic and usage within the application using analytical tools integrated into the SCRIBZEE® Application. However, please note that this data is completely anonymous. This means that the link between the data and the user has been broken and under no circumstances can we trace the data back to the user.
Data collected during your use of the SCRIBZEE® Website
We may collect personal data from you when you use the SCRIBZEE® Website, including when you contact us via the contact form.
In addition, please note that we use cookies on the SCRIBZEE® Website through which we collect some navigation data. If you wish to learn more about the use of cookies on the SCRIBZEE® Website, please read
the cookie policy.
