We believe that the risk associated with the personal data we process on the basis of our legitimate interests is not excessive or too intrusive. In particular, we have put in place measures to protect your rights by applying appropriate retention periods and ensuring appropriate security controls.
No profiling will be carried out and, more generally, no automated decisions will be taken on the basis of the data collected.
4. Commercial communications and opt-out
We may send you administrative email (emails regarding changes in the operation of SCRIBZEE®, in this Privacy Policy etc.).
In addition, if you consented to it, you may receive emails containing offers and information regarding SCRIBZEE®-compatible products and/or products or services of our partner EVERNOTE.
You can withdraw your consent and request not to receive commercial emails by using the unsubscribe link at the end of each message you receive.
5. Retention period
We retain your personal data for the length of time your user account is active and then for three years after your last authentication to your SCRIBZEE® account from the SCRIBZEE® Application or the SCRIBZEE® Website.
Before permanently deleting your personal data, we will send you an email to suggest that you manually save your data in PDF format from the SCRIBZEE® Application or Website. You will have 3 months to reconnect and manually retrieve your data. After this period, your data will be permanently destroyed, and your account will be closed.
6. Recipients of personal data and transfers
We will share your personal data with third parties when required by law, when necessary to manage our contractual relationship with you or when we have another legitimate interest in doing so. We will share your personal data with the following categories of third parties:
The French company HAMELIN SAS which is the editor of SCRIBZEE® and a subsidiary of HOLDHAM;
The Cloud platform provider on which your handwritten notes will be stored;
Service providers who support our business such as computing providers and logistic partners.
Please note that your personal data will never be marketed. We will never rent or sell your personal data.
We may also disclose your personal data to third parties:
if we sell or buy a business or assets, we may disclose your personal data to the potential seller or buyer of that business or assets; and
if HOLDHAM or part of its assets are acquired by a third party, in which case the personal data held by HOLDHAM will be part of the transferred assets.
7. Data transfers outside the European Economic Area
We may transfer your personal data outside the European Economic Area ("EEA") in the following cases:
As part of the management of our customer base, we may share your contact information with a company located in the United States that has joined the Privacy Shield program established by the United States Department of Commerce;
As part of our use of the Google Analytics cookie, we may share your login information with Google that has joined the Privacy Shield program established by the United States Department of Commerce.
Please be aware that we take the necessary precautions to ensure that these providers implement adequate safeguards and comply with strict conditions regarding confidentiality, use and data protection.
10. Public authorities
We may disclose your personal data to public authorities legally empowered to investigate illegal activities that may entail our liability, your liability or the liability of another a user of SCRIBZEE®.
11. Your rights
As a data subject, you have certain rights with regard to your personal data. These rights are not absolute and each of these rights are subject to certain conditions in accordance with the GDPR and applicable national laws.
The right of access:
you have the right to obtain from us confirmation that your personal data is or is not being processed by us, as well as certain other information (similar to that provided in this Privacy Policy) about how it is used. You also have the right to access all your personal data via SCRIBZEE®.
The right of rectification:
you can rectify or correct certain personal data in SCRIBZEE® if they are inaccurate or incomplete.
However, please note that your account is inherently linked to your email address. We are not able to change the email address that is linked to your account.
The right to erase:
also known as the "right to forget", this right allows you to erase or request the erasure or deletion of your personal data when, for example, there is no compelling reason for us to continue using them or their use is illegal. However, this is not a general right to erasure and there are some exceptions, for example when we have to use the information to defend a legal action or to be able to comply with a legal obligation.
You may at any time decide to permanently and irrevocably delete your account and personal data. To do this, you must access the delete feature of your account located in the SCRIBZEE® Application / Profile / Account Options.
Please note that uninstalling the SCRIBZEE® Application from your smartphone will not delete your account and personal data. In addition, for security reasons, we refuse to delete an account when this deletion has been requested from us by email or via the contact form.
The right to restrict the processing:
you have the right to "block" or prevent the further use of your personal data when we assess a rectification request or as an alternative to deletion. When processing is limited, we can always keep your personal data, but we cannot use it further.
The right to data portability:
The right to data portability: you have the right to obtain and reuse certain personal data for your own purposes across different organisations (being separate data controllers). This only applies to personal data that you have provided to us, personal data we process with your consent and for the purposes of contract performance, which are processed by automated means. In this case, we will provide you with a copy of your data in a structured format, commonly used and readable by a machine or (where technically possible) we may transmit your data directly to another controller. In addition, at any time you can manually save the images of your handwritten notes in PDF format from SCRIBZEE®.
The right of opposition:
you have the right to object to certain types of processing, for reasons relating to your particular situation, at any time, insofar as such processing takes place for the purpose of legitimate interests pursued by HOLDHAM. We will be allowed to continue to process personal data if we can demonstrate that the processing is justified by compelling and legitimate reasons that outweigh your interests, rights and freedoms or if we need it for the establishment, exercise or defence of legal proceedings. If you object to the processing of your personal data for direct marketing purposes, you can unsubscribe from email communications by using the "unsubscribe" button at the bottom of each communication.
The right to withdraw your consent:
when we process your personal data on the basis of your consent, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time. However, such withdrawal shall not affect the lawfulness of the processing operation which took place before such withdrawal. You can unsubscribe from e-mail communications by using the "unsubscribe" button at the bottom of each communication.
The right to provide us with instructions on the use of your personal data after your death:
you have the right to provide us with instructions on the management (e. g. storage, deletion and disclosure) of your data after your death. You can change or revoke your instructions at any time.
If you would like more information about your rights, if you would like to exercise more information about your rights, if you would like to exercise one of them or if you have a complaint, please contact us at the following address:
scribzee.privacy@hamelinbrands.com
If you are not satisfied with our response to your complaint or if you believe that the processing of your personal data does not comply with applicable data protection laws, you may file a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority. If you reside in the European Union, you can file this claim with the supervisory authority of the country in which you reside. If you do not reside in the European Union, you can file your complaint with the Commission Informatique et Libertés (CNIL), which is the data protection authority in France.
We will review all such requests and provide our response within the time limits provided by applicable law. Please note, however, that some personal data may be exempted from such requests in certain circumstances, in particular if we are to continue to process your personal data for its legitimate interests or to comply with a legal obligation.
You will not have to pay any fees to access your personal data (or to exercise any other rights). However, we may charge a reasonable fee if your request for access is clearly unfounded or excessive. We may also refuse to comply with the request in such circumstances.
We may need to ask you for specific information to help us confirm your identity and guarantee your right to access this information (or to exercise your other rights). This is another appropriate security measure to ensure that personal data is not disclosed to a person who is not entitled to receive it.
12. Security
We and our service provider Microsoft Azure Cloud have adopted physical, electronic and administrative security measures to protect your personal data, including the use of a threat, attack and password monitoring tool, and encryption techniques to secure access to your personal data. In particular, please note that Microsoft Azure Cloud encrypts your personal data stored cold in the cloud with an AES 256-bit algorithm and also encrypts the connection between your smartphone and its servers with SSL and TLS 1.2 protocols.
We also provide instant replication of your data in two Microsoft Azure Cloud data centers to ensure the highest availability of your data.
In addition, we limit access to personal data to authorized employees of Holdham, Hamelin SAS and our service providers who need to know this information to operate, develop or improve SCRIBZEE® services.
